==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hod
<hw>Hod</hw> <pr>(h⟦ocr⟧d)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Prov. E. for
<ets>hold</ets>, <it>i. e.</it>, that which holds. See
<er>Hold</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A kind of wooden tray with a
handle, having V-shaped trough, made of wood or metal, attached to a
long handle and usually carried over the shoulder; it is a tool used by
construction workers for carrying bricks or mortar.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A utensil for holding coal; a coal
scuttle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>hod carrier</ent>⟦br⟧
